a. What is an issue?
GitHub Issues are items you can create in a repository to plan, discuss and track work.

b. What is a pull request?
to copy your change into the git

c. How do I open up a pull request?
in vscode, after the change , commit and sync, and pull the request via github

d. Give me a step by step guide on how to add someone to your repository.
select the add collabrator in the rapos, and then enter their emails.

e. What is the difference between git and GitHub?
git stands for the way that coders how they track their difference versions or features.
github is a website based repo hosting service.

f. What does git diff do?
the command shows the difference between commits

g. What is the main branch?
The root folder

h. Besides our initial commit if it is a new repository, should we directly push our changes directly into the main branch?
yes, when we made new features, merge back to main
